# Build-context exclusions for the client image (client/Dockerfile).
#
# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .` after `npm install` in a fresh linux node
# builder. Without this file the host's node_modules (built for the host OS/arch,
# e.g. a macOS/arm64 esbuild binary) overlays the image's freshly-installed
# linux modules, breaking `vite build` with an esbuild host/binary mismatch; and
# a gitignored .env would be copied into the builder layers. Keep this list in
# sync with client/.gitignore's build artifacts (C10).
node_modules
dist
.env
.env.*
*.local

# VCS / editor / OS noise -- never needed in the image
.git
.gitignore
.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode
npm-debug.log*
